Standard and Poor's Corp said it raisedto B from CCC 268.9 mln dlrs of equipment trust certificates ofTexas Air Corp's Eastern Air Lines Inc unit.    S and P cited its new policy on rating secured airline debtwith special protection under Section 1110 of the BankruptcyCode. But the agency cautioned this did not reflect a change inthe unit's underlying credit strength.    The certificates and 225.9 mln dlrs of CC subordinated debtremain on S/P creditwatch with positive implications. Easternlost 130.8 mln dlrs in 1986 because of competition and customeruncertainty over its future, S and P noted. Reuter&#3;